{{Infobox academic | honorific_prefix = | name = Margaret Cicely Langton Greene | honorific_suffix = {{post-nominal|unlinked=FRCSLT}} {{post nominals|UK|OBE}} | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = 1913 | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | occupation = {{plainlist| * Speech Therapist }} | awards = | alma_mater = | thesis_year = | discipline = | sub_discipline = Voice disorders | workplaces = {{plainlist| *RCSLT }} }}
'''Margaret Cicely Langton Greene''' {{post-nominal|unlinked=FRCSLT}} {{post nominals|UK|OBE}} was a British [[speech and language therapist]].
She was elected a Fellow of the [[Royal College of Speech and Language Therapists]] in 1957.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rcslt.org/honours_roll_call_1945-2016 |title=RCSLT Honours Roll Call |publisher=Royal College of Speech and Lanuage Therapists |accessdate=20 October 2018}}</ref> She was also the editor of its ''Bulletin'' and its journal, ''Speech'', in the mid- 1950s.<ref>{{cite journal |url=https://www.rcslt.org/docs/bulletin/2005/Oct_2005 |title=1981-1990: The Thatcher years |journal=Bulletin of the Royal College of Speech and Language Therapists |volume=642 |date=October 2005}}</ref> Margaret Greene received an OBE in the [[1987 Birthday Honours]] for services to Speech Therapy.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thegazette.co.uk/London/issue/50948/supplement/1 |date=12 June 1987 |title=SUPPLEMENT TO The London Gazette |publisher=The Gazette: Official Public Record |page=9}}</ref> In 1957 Green published ''The Voice and its Disorders'', which represented a major contribution to the clinical assessment and treatment of voice disorders and was amongt the few texts available on the subject at the time.<ref>{{cite journal |author1=Meyerson, M. D. |date=2003 |title=Book Review: Greene & Mathieson's The Voice and Its Disorders (6th edition) |journal=Topics in Language Disorders |volume=23 |issue=1 |pages=68&dash;69}}</ref> The book is now into it's 6th edition, most recently updated and re-published in 2001 by Lesley Mathieson.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.worldcat.org/title/greene-and-mathiesons-the-voice-and-its-disorders/oclc/247904975&referer=brief_results |title=Greene and Mathieson's the voice and its disorders |publisher=WorldCat |accessdate=20 October 2018}}</ref>
==Publications== *1957. ''The Voice and its Disorders'' *1960. ''Learning to Talk. A guide for parents''. London, William Heinemann.
